I can’t believe Demi is talking about her experience with God and her faith and I dreamt about THIS almost a year ago. I felt the urge of telling her what my dream was about and I sent Demi a message (even though I know she may not see it) because I felt God was telling me to let her know so I did. So I am sharing with you guys what I told her and hope she can somehow see it ( I wish I could put the screenshot)

Hi Demi! I've thinking this for a while now, because I wasn't sure if you were going to see this but if you don't it's okay, I tried I least. A few weeks ago, aprox 3 weeks from now, I dreamt about you. It was SUPER ODD, because you were somehow in Nicaragua, where I am from, and we were staying at the same place but I was with my Family. In certain moment, I was walking through a hall and I saw you, you were with a tall man practicing something with him, I think it was Judo, I got closer and I feel in my heart I needed to tell you something so I asked you "can I hug you?" And you looked at me surprised and you said yes and I did, and I whispered to your ear, "Demi, whatever you are going through, you'll be able to make it. You are strong but you have to truly believe it in your heart and keep that strength so nobody hurts you. You are beautiful, don't let people bring or anything bring you down" I stopped hugging you and you looked at me, YOU WERE CRYING, and you said:
This is what I needed.
I don't know if you believe In God or have any other believing but I do believe in God and BELIEVE me for some reason I truly felt the urge or telling you this, I event told by boyfriend this weird feeling and he told me, "fuck it, do it, tell her." So I hope this somehow helps if you get to see it:)

snippet.textDisplay: I am saying this not to be judgmental because I have gotten botox and won't stop getting it (until wrinkles are normalized? maybe not even then) but no one is talking about "face positivity." Ashley's forehead doesn't move. We can talk all day about bodies and that is hugely important.  But no one is talking about the "non-surgeries" people are doing to their face-- me included! We are conditioning women to believe that your face must not have a wrinkle. A forehead cannot move. Everything must be lifted. Perhaps the botox/injection conversation isn't as important nor damaging as the body conversation but why isn't it part of the conversation.
